@page "/privacy-policy"

@using GoldenBarbers.Client.Pages

<div class="policy-text">
    <h1>Privacy Policy - Golden Barbers</h1>
    <br />
    <h2>Last Updated: 20.03.2026</h2>
    <br />
    <p>
        Golden Barbers (“we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy and
        is committed to protecting your personal data in accordance with the
        EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and applicable Finnish data protection legislation.
        <br />
        This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect personal information when
        you use the Golden Barbers website and booking system.
    </p>

    <h3>1. Data Controller</h3>
    <br />
    <p>The data controller responsible for your personal data is: </p>
    <h4>Golden Barbers</h4>
    <p>
        Arkadiankatu 3
        <br />
        00100 Helsinki
        Finland
    </p>

    <p>Email: info@goldenbarbers.fi</p>

    <h3>2. Personal Data We Collect</h3>
    <br />
    <p>When you use our website or make a reservation, we may collect the following information: </p>

    <h4>Information you provide</h4>

    <ul>
        <li>Name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Appointment booking details</li>
        <li>Preferred barber or service</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Automatically collected information</h4>

    <p>When you visit the website, some technical data may be collected automatically, such as:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Browser type and language</li>
        <li>Device information</li>
        <li>Website usage data</li>
        <li>Cookies and analytics data</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Purpose of Processing Personal Data</h3>
    <br />
    <p>We process personal data for the following purposes: </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Managing and confirming appointments</li>
        <li>Providing customer service</li>
        <li>Communicating booking confirmations or changes</li>
        <li>Improving website functionality and user experience</li>
        <li>Maintaining website security</li>
        <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        Under GDPR, we process personal data based on one or
        more of the following legal grounds:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Performance of a contract</strong> - when processing is
            necessary to manage your appointment booking.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Legitimate interest</strong> - to improve our services
            and maintain website security
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Consent</strong> - where you have explicitly given consent
            (for example optional cookies).
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Legal obligation</strong> - where processing is
            required by law.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. Data Retention</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill
        the purposes described in this policy.
    </p>
    <p>Typical retention periods: </p>

    <ul>
        <li>
            Appointment data: retained for service management and
            business records.
        </li>
        <li>
            Customer contact information: retained as long as needed
            for booking services.
        </li>
        <li>
            Analytics data: retained according to analytics
            provider policies.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <p>Data is deleted or anonymized when it is no longer required.</p>

    <h3>6. Data Sharing and Third Parties</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        We do not sell or rent personal data to third parties.
        <br />
        Personal data may be shared with trusted service
        providers when necessary to operate the website
        and the booking system, such as:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Website hosting providers</li>
        <li>Cloud infrastructure providers</li>
        <li>Email service providers</li>
        <li>Analytics services</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        All third parties are required to process personal
        data in compliance with GDPR and applicable data
        protection laws.
    </p>

    <h3>7. International data transfers</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        If personal data is transferred outside the European Economic Area (EEA),
        appropriate safeguards will be implemented to ensure the protection of
        your data in accordance with GDPR.
    </p>

    <h3>8. Your Rights Under GDPR</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        Under GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your
        personal data:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Right of access</strong> - request a copy of your personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Right of rectification</strong> - request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Right of erasure ("right to be forgotten")</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Right of restrict processing</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Right to object to processing</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <p>You may exercise these rights by contacting us at: </p>

    <a href="mailto:info@goldenbarbers.fi">info@goldenbarbers.fi</a>

    <h3>9. Cookies</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        Our website may use cookies to improve user experience
        and analyze website usage.
        <br />
        Cookies may be used for:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Website functionality</li>
        <li>Analytics</li>
        <li>Performance monitoring</li>
    </ul>

    <p>You can control cookie preferences through your browser settings.</p>

    <h3>10. Data Security</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect personal data against unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration.
        <br />
        These measures may include:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Encrypted connections (HTTPS)</li>
        <li>Secure server infrastructure</li>
        <li>Restricted data access</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes
        in legal requirements or our services.
        <br />
        The latest version will always be available on the Golden Barbers
        website.
    </p>

    <h3>12. Complaints</h3>
    <br />
    <p>
        If you believe your personal data has been processed unlawfully,
        you have the right to lodge a complaint with the Finnish
        supervisory authority:
        <br />
        Office of the Data Protection Ombudsman
        (Tietosuojavaltuutetun toimisto)
        <br />
        Website: https://tietosuoja.fi
    </p>

    <p>
        If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy or
        the processing of personal data, please contact us at:
        <br />
        <a href="mailto:info@goldenbarbers.fi">info@goldenbarbers.fi</a>
    </p>
</div>
